# SwiftFormat configuration for Rainplay iOS.
# The Xcode build phase runs this in --lint --lenient mode (warnings only, never
# rewrites on build). Apply formatting manually with:  swiftformat .
#
# Deliberately a curated allow-list (via --rules): the codebase is hand-styled
# (aligned Dutch comments, concise one-line ifs, explicit returns), and
# SwiftFormat's full default set fights that and would produce a huge churn diff.
# We enable only safe, low-churn, semantics-preserving hygiene rules here.
# NOTE: redundantNilInit is intentionally NOT enabled — it would strip `= nil`
# from optional properties that rely on it for the synthesized memberwise init.

--swiftversion 6.0

--rules sortImports,duplicateImports,numberFormatting,trailingSpace,consecutiveBlankLines,blankLinesAtStartOfScope,blankLinesAtEndOfScope,linebreakAtEndOfFile,emptyBraces,redundantParens,redundantGet,spaceInsideBrackets,spaceInsideParens

# Exclude generated / non-source paths.
--exclude **/.build,DerivedData,**/*.xcassets
